summary: what with all the blending of the lines between pokemon and humans, especially with pokemon like abra (psychic child that just...
body: what with all the blending of the lines between pokemon and humans, especially with pokemon like abra (psychic child that just sort of turned into a pokemon), phantump (soul of a child who died in a forest possessing a stump), and yamask (soul of a human that carries its own face around as a mask), as well as pokemon that can replicate the appearances of other things to the point people and other pokemon get legitimately confused (such as voltorb, foongus, and amoongus near perfectly resembling pokeballs), and the fact that pokemon can learn to speak english if they want (team rocket meowth), i think it could be argued that nurse joys and officer jennys are both breeds of pokemon that just very very closely resemble humans

question: Agency 259
answer:
White finds Black sitting cross-legged on the floor, frowning down at numerous bills spread out in front of him. “Whatcha doin’?”

“Math,” he grunts. “I wanna…” He stops, realizing who he’s talking to. “… Pay for something.”

She can tell he doesn’t want her to know, so she pats his shoulder before walking away. She stops just on the other side of the door, however, to listen in as he talks to Tula.

“That was close,” Black tells his Pokemon. “Prez can’t know this is for a nice dinner with her.”

White smiles before saying loudly, “Well, don’t keep me waiting!” 

It might’ve been rude, but she knows that got him all flustered so it was worth it.

question: pokeshipping 25
answer:
”What’s this?” Misty asks, noticing the wrapped parcel sitting on the kitchen table.

”It’s a present,” Dawn answers with a smirk. She picks it up and hands it to Misty, though it might have been because she and May required more room for their Contest paperwork.

“It’s from Ash,” May adds.

”Like I couldn’t tell.” Misty rolls her eyes. The sloppy handwriting on the label tells her as much, as well as the groan coming from the living room. She rips open the package and stares down at the seashell necklace now sitting in her palm.

“You did this?” she hollers, as though in disbelief. “I could kiss you right now!”

“I’m waiting, then,” Ash mumbles, and the three girls exchange half-amused, half-shocked looks before Misty runs to catch him before he disappears.

Sableye And Houndoom respectedly.
At first it...
body:
The Rotom Dex

So in USUM, the pokedex entry for mega evolution is dark as fuck. Like these two:

Sableye And Houndoom respectedly.

At first it was thought that Professor Kukui was in charge of the entries, but a conversation with someone in Maile City said that it was “created by a young lad in Kalos”.

Understandably, Professor Sycamore was suspect no. 1.

But why would he make those entries so dark? He’s fond of mega evolution, isn’t he?

Well, regardless of who exactly physically made The Pokédex, it’s probably a definite fact that Sycamore did play a part in the entries. After all, why wouldn’t you approach the mega evolution expert on a mega pokedex entry?

But why is it so dark??? 🧐

@frosted-daffodils

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

body:
Rhyhorn brain: Rotom is a Legendary because it's a secret Pokemon you can only find one of in Gen 4, it has special forms, doesn't evolve, and has the Legendary Pokemon battle music

Metagross brain: Rotom is a non-Legendary Pokemon that can be bred and caught in the wild as a common species, and is used by NPCs

Arceus brain: Rotom is an Ekans evolution because its name is a backwards word
